CLASSICAL SWINE FEVER IN SPAIN
---------------------------------
(Date of last previously reported outbreak: July 1998).
Emergency report
Translation of the information received on 14 June 2001 from Dr Ignacio
Sanchez Esteban, Deputy Director General of Animal Health, Ministry of
Agriculture, Fisheries and Food, Madrid:
Report date: 14 Jun 2001
Nature of diagnosis: clinical and laboratory
Date of suspicion: 12 Jun 2001
Date of confirmation of diagnosis: 14 Jun 2001
Outbreaks:
Location Soses district, Lerida province, Catalonia Autonomous Community
Number of Outbreaks: 1
Description of affected population: fattening pigs (no breeding pigs)
Total number of animals in the outbreak:
species/ susceptible/ cases/ deaths/ destroyed/ slaughtered
sui/ 2053/ 195/ 65*/ 1988/ 0
* During the past 15 days (including 45 pigs that died during the past 6 days).
Diagnosis:
A. Laboratory where diagnosis was made: national reference laboratory for
classical swine fever (CISA-INIA, Madrid)
B. Diagnostic tests used: antigen detection by ELISA and virus detection by
PCR (primers specific to classical swine fever)
Epidemiology:
A. Source of agent / origin of infection: investigations under way.
B. Other epidemiological details: five pig farms have been identified
within a 1-km radius of the outbreak, with a total number of 150 breeding
pigs and 6,700 fattening pigs.
Control measures:
- classical swine fever is a notifiable disease in Spain, subject to an
official control programme; vaccination is prohibited
- stamping out was applied on 13 and 14 Jun 2001
- quarantine and movement control inside the country
- testing
--
